artists.name: Kalkidan Tilahun (Lili)
artists.bio: Kalkidan Tilahun, popularly known as "Lili," is a prominent Ethiopian gospel singer. She rose to fame in the 1990s and is considered one of the most well-known singers of her time in Ethiopia. Currently, she resides in the United States. Her brothers, Dagmawi (Dagi) Tilahun and Dr. Lealem (Laly) Tilahun, are also well-known singers.

artists.name: Pastor Tekeste Getnet
artists.bio: Pastor Tekeste Getnet was a renowned Ethiopian Protestant singer and songwriter whose music has left a lasting impact on the gospel landscape. While detailed biographical information remains somewhat scarce, it is known that he was born in the Wolayta zone of the Southern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples' Region of Ethiopia. He was a beloved figure in the Ethiopian Christian community, known for his powerful voice and heartfelt lyrics that touched the lives of many.

artists.name: Yidnekachew Teka
artists.bio: Yidnekachew Teka is an Ethiopian Protestant singer and worship minister. He has released at least two albums: "Chekolebegn Lebie Liyagegneh" (ቸኮለብኝ ልቤ ሊያገኝህ), which translates to "My heart is in a hurry to find you," and "Iyesus" (ኢየሱስ), meaning "Jesus," released in 2023.
